```java
public class BondDuration {

    private static final double ERROR = 0.0001;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        double presentValue = 1000.0; //Given present value of Bond
        double couponRate = 0.05; //Annual coupon rate of 5%
        int yearsToMaturity = 5; //Years until bond matures
        double annualInterestRate = 0.03; //Annual interest rate used for discounting

        double macaulayDuration = calculateMacaulayDuration(presentValue, couponRate, yearsToMaturity, annualInterestRate);
        double modifiedDuration = calculateModifiedDuration(macaulayDuration, annualInterestRate);

        System.out.println("Macaulay Duration: " + macaulayDuration);
        System.out.println("Modified Duration: " + modifiedDuration);
    }

    private static double calculateMacaulayDuration(double presentValue, double couponRate, int yearsToMaturity, double interestRate){
        double cumulativeCashFlow = 0.0;
        for(int i=1; i <= yearsToMaturity; i++){
            double cashFlow = (couponRate * presentValue) / Math.pow((1 + interestRate), i);
            cumulativeCashFlow += i * cashFlow;
        }
        cumulativeCashFlow += yearsToMaturity * presentValue / Math.pow((1 + interestRate), yearsToMaturity);
        return cumulativeCashFlow / presentValue;
    }

    private static double calculateModifiedDuration(double macaulayDuration, double interestRate){
        return macaulayDuration / (1 + interestRate);
    }
}
```
This program calculates the Macaulay Duration by summing the present value of each future coupon payment, multiplied by the time it will be received, divided by the present value of the bond. The Modified Duration is then calculated by dividing the Macaulay Duration by one plus the interest rate. Please adjust the presentValue, couponRate, yearsToMaturity, and annualInterestRate as needed for your bond calculations.

Please note that the calculation assumes annual coupon payments. If your bond has a different coupon payment frequency, you will need to adjust the code accordingly. For example, for semiannual payments, you would need to halve the couponRate and interestRate and double the yearsToMaturity.

